    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-29T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="33"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/1151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-29T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 29, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. My 100, July 24, 11 a.m. President Olaya and Minister of Industries have
                    signed petroleum regulating decree. The decree, <pb facs="0138" n="18"
                        xml:id="pg_18"/> however, has not yet been published in the <hi
                        rend="italic">Diario</hi>. It is highly satisfactory. Please inform Mr.
                    Rublee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
